SpaceX API Calls – Data Acquisition Process
🔑 Key Points:
API Source: SpaceX-API – a public, open-source RESTful API.

Purpose: To collect real-time and historical launch, rocket, and site data directly from the SpaceX backend.

Format: JSON → Pandas DataFrame (cleaned, transformed, merged).

Why API?: Ensures up-to-date and accurate information without relying solely on static files.

🔗 API Endpoints Used:
Endpoint	Description
/v4/launches	Launch outcomes, payloads, dates
/v4/rockets	Booster versions, rocket types
/v4/launchpads	Launch site names & details

🔁 Data Retrieval Flow:
mermaid
复制
编辑
flowchart TD
    A[Start] --> B[Send GET request to SpaceX API]
    B --> C[Receive JSON response]
    C --> D[Convert JSON to Pandas DataFrame]
    D --> E[Normalize & Filter relevant fields]
    E --> F[Save to CSV or merge with existing datasets]
    F --> G[Data ready for EDA & Dashboard]
